      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027ll eventually want something that\u0027s platform independent, anyway.\n\nI had been thinking you\u0027d want to use Android\u0027s ThreadBase. To do that you\u0027d need to leave it up to the client somehow to handle threading. If you want this to all live in Skia, though, perhaps you\u0027ll want to use SkExecutor::MakeFIFOThreadPool, which takes care of the queue behavior.\n\nIt doesn\u0027t appear to (currently) do anything regarding priority, though.",
